text: Astoria Boulevard, at the southwest corner of 90th Street, showing old Public School No. 10, also known at one time as the Bowery Bay District School and the Frogtown school. It was erected in 1879. May, 1923. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Astoria Boulevard, at the S.E. corner of 90th Street, showing the Old Frogtown School which was also known as the Bowery Bay District School. It was erected in 1879 and was still standing in 1927 when it was known as P.S. No. 10. This is a set of two views. Views 1 and 2: May 1923. Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
